{
	"name": "Signature Deed",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/sundries/documents/blueprint-helmet.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>At 18th level, once per long rest, you may declare a Signature Deed, a mythic moment that defines you. Choose one effect below. It takes no action, lasts 1 minute, and ends early if you are incapacitated.</p><p>While it is active, you also emit an aura of mythic flame in a 10-foot radius, shedding bright light, and you may add your Charisma modifier to all saving throws.</p><p></p><h2>No One Falls Today</h2><p>Allies within your aura cannot have advantage on death saving throws, and if they roll 15 or more on their death save, they regain 1 HP.</p><p></p><h2>By My Name Alone</h2><p>Each round, you may mark one creature as part of this legend (no action). That creature has disadvantage on attacks against anyone but you, and you gain resistance to its damages.</p><p></p><h2>This Blade Ends the Tale</h2><p>Once per turn when you hit with a weapon attack, the target must make a flat check (DC 3). On a failure, they are doomed and die at the end of their next turn unless they manage to kill you or make you unconscious.</p>",
