			"description": "<ul><li><p>A doomed creature dies at a time determined by the Narrator, or within 13 ([[/r 2d12]]) hours.</p></li><li><p>A doomed creature continues to be doomed even after it dies. Magic equivalent to a 7th-level or higher spell can remove the doomed condition (such as @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.acw9pizt7nhzdwdl]{regenerate} cast on a living creature, @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.zontlhypt3b5gk6z]{resurrection}, @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.d4gqwm4bxoklygp6]{true resurrection}, or @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.pe52jryde7ljobzq]{wish}).</p></li></ul>",
